          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Monoenergetic gamma rays produced by thermal  neutron",
                " capture  have  been used to study photoneutron cross",
                " sections of the isotopes Ta-181,  Li-7,  Li-6, C-13,",
                " and  B-10  for  g-ray energies between threshold and",
                " 10.8 MeV.  Some cross sections  were  obtained  with",
                " uncertainties  as  low  as  10%.  Wherever possible,",
                " these  cross  sections  are  compared   with   those",
                " obtained  by  other  methods.  The threshold for the",
                " Ta-181(gamma,n) reaction has been determined  to  be",
                " 7.64(0.04)  MeV.  Information  about  the  radiative",
                " widths of the 7.47 MeV level in Li-7  and  the  8.89",
                " MeV level in B-10 is presented."
              ]
            }
          ],
